caption: Love the food. Love the drinks. And my kids are so well behaved. We are thinking of moving in. :)

We went to Bistronomic for Restaurant Week Brunch for a wonderful three course meal with French wine. We will return again in the near future. Being Francophiles, we loved the French touch to the food, which the bistro type food is kicked up a several notches to the level of true French restaurant. Service was very pleasant and welcoming adding to the experience.
Wow how did I miss this place?  It totally wowed us.  Will be back!

Everything a restaurant should be.  Superb balance of professional service and original food presentation.  Delicious food, in a classy setting.  The front of the restaurant does not do it justice. A refreshing change from the normal steak, pizza/italian joint.  Great wine list too!
I love Bistronomic! The food is delicious and the owners are so friendly! Definitely recommend!
A great place for brunch. Do not forget to ask for the specials of the day. You won’t be disappointed.
Absolutely delicious!!! 10/10 recommend
Wonderful brunch without breaking the bank, but the ambiance would make you think you were going to spend much more! Friendly staff and good mimosas 😊
Excellent French toast and I loved the bottomless mimosas

The location is cool. The Ambience is nice. The bottomless mimosas were great. Tuna Tartare was pretty wonderful. Ordered Le French Burger and they brought it to me with raw beef. The brought out a whole new plate and it was fantastic.
Everything we ordered was good!
Outstanding experience!  Service was wonderful and the food was delicious.  Bottomless Mimosas do NOT disappoint!
i was super full. i look forward to a return trip. this place has a cool feel to it.
Beet goat cheese salad was amazing! Very friendly staff who took us in before they were about to close!!

This place was GREAT! I researched restaurants for quite a while before deciding on on Bistronomic and I have to pat myself on the back. Great downtown location and the prices were definitely reasonable given the quality of the food. They offer small, medium and large plates, which allows you to taste a little bit of everything. There were 4 of us and we ended up sharing a bunch of stuff. My friend even ordered another entree after we finished the first "round" because everything was so delicious. We will absolutely be back. Highly recommended!

We enjoyed our Christmas dinner from Bistronomic. We picked it up the day before and it came with good reheating and plating instructions, although we had to significantly lengthen the amount of time in the oven for the meat.  The quality of the meat however was absolutely spectacular. How a piece of meat can still be that tender and soft after being cooled down and reheated is beyond me, but it was really spectacular.  Deducting one star because the food overall was quite pricey and the portions are authentically French (i.e. on the smaller side).
Their parmesan truffle fries are amazing. I also had the linguine with salmon and saffron. I smelled the saffron from another table and decided I had to order it. I was not disappointed.
everyone at our table was glad to be there. the service was very kind and attentive.
We like Bistronomic because of the French atmosphere and the food, prepared in a French style, has always been excellent.. Oh and the White Chocolate Bread Pudding was awesome.

Great French offerings and amazing service...we did a pickup as we were in a hotel, all servers and hostess really hustling and all with great attitudes!  Superb food, amazing preparation!  Please support this restaurant, you wont be disappointed!

Great dinner, great food, great service. The menu is rich, the wine list is very interesting. We had the couscous of the day that was great. There is a patio outside with gaz heaters that work great despite the cold arriving.
Similar to a cafe in Las Vegas I loved.
Great place for a boozy brunch outdoors! Their croque monsieur was extremely tasty and the fries were perfectly crisp!
Visited about four, it was not full. Looking forward to going back again. It has a great interior. Food is like a restaurant in Jacksonville I loved.

Great French food. Authentic and great service. Check it out.
We enjoyed a lovely dinner! Only thing was they were very busy but I guess that's a good thing these days.

Lovely Sunday brunch for two out-of-towners. We sat outside and the heat lamps were perfect. Very attentive service and excellent food. Easy street parking as well as nearby garage parking. Loved the smoked salmon avocado toast, savory crepes and short rib hash. Marked as ‘saved’ in my list for sure. Would come again!
There was fast and courteous service. Prices are fair I would say.

I'm eternally grateful to the owner, Lulu, and her team at Bistronomic. Door Dash cancelled my Phenomenal French Affair (a three-course meal experience where multiple restaurants, including Bistronomic, come together to prepare a fine dining experience for folks at home) order 10 minutes before the delivery time and 30 minutes before my guests arrived.  Multiple conversations with Door Dash still couldn't resolve the failure to deliver my meal. Bistronomic was contacted by Door Dash and immediately called me. Lulu not only apologized for the inconvenience (though Door Dash owned this) but offered to cook the whole meal at Bistronomic and inform the other restaurants who were part of the Phenomenal French Affair that she would help resolved by stepping in. Lulu again made arrangements with Door Dash to pick up the cooked meal so we'd have dinner to serve our guests. But yet again, Door Dash failed to arrive and fulfill the delivery. So, Lulu herself drove to our home (25 minutes from Bistronomic) and delivered the meal. Everything was perfect and our evening was saved. We cannot thank Bistronomic enough for their professionalism, high-end customer service and delicious three-course meal. Please add Bistronomic on your list to order from and dine at--in my book they are now best in class. Door Dash on the other hand has lost my business.

Amazing atmosphere and fantastic food. I am from Montreal and grew up in the French culture  and this is one of the best French restaurants I have been to. Our favorites were the the Onion soup, duck confit and St-Andre cheese. Mussels and tartare were amazing too. Next time i’ll try the escargot and liver mousse. Must go!!
Best French food in the city
Great bottomless mimosas and the French burger with fries was amazing
Always a great experience.  Busy tonight but well managed.  Highly recommend!
this location is one of my favorites. next time i'll be back with my relatives.

Used to be one of my favorite spots for brunch. Loved organizing monthly brunches for my book club here. Was excited to try their dinner menu with my husband and was greatly disappointed. I ordered the salmon which was dry and burnt and when I asked the waiter to take my plate away (we never asked him to not charge us for it) I was just not happy with my meal and needed him to take it away from the table so I can eat some of my husband’s food. He kept arguing with me that it’s not burnt and refused to take it. Anyways, good place if you want to be disrespected, Eventually when my husband finished his plate they took the our plates. He disappeared for a while and finally came back with the check. We ended paying for the burnt salmon that was not touched! Anyways, ISorry guys, but I will never be back even for the brunches. You lost a regular due to one of your waiter refusal to to do something as basic as removing a plate.
I love visiting here. Quick, helpful, and friendly service. The bill was fair.
Incredible croque madame and fries!
It was so fresh. Quick, helpful, and friendly service. Prices are decent for the quality.
Best service ever

Surprisingly good food and great staff. Tried something new the layers in this Croque Madame was amazing the picture doesn't do it justice!! Bottomless mimosas add a nice touch!

This was truly one of the best dining experiences I've ever had. It was everything-the wonderful greeting when we walked up, the attentive and knowledgeable waiter and staff and every course being delicious. I honestly can't say enough positive things. We are visiting from Pittsburgh and every time I return to Chicago I will be back. Thank you for a very memorable experience.🥰❤
Ilir K was AMAZING. Will be back just because of him. amazing experience!!!
Amazing staff! Food is great. Brunch was amazing
Food was so delicious. The place has a cool feel to it.

A most delightful meal highlighted by a table side visit from Chef Marcial Noguier! A French "must" in Chicago highlighting incredibly fresh, locally grown ingrediants married with amazing culinary finesse!

Been here twice now and food was awesome the first time and even better the second!  Have eaten at so many restaurants in Chicago and this is one of the best brunches I have had.  From being greeted by Lulu to having tremendous service after being seated, AUCD mimosas, and the Wild Mushroom Omelet is OUT OF THIS WORLD GOOD and Eggs Benedict is super good and the muffins taste homemade added with a little sweetness that goes so well with the dish.  The breakfast potatoes are the best in the city hands down! So excited to go for dinner this week and Ilir is a great server and always on top of everything!  5 Stars all the way!
very delicious. looking forward to a return visit. this place has a good design. menu is similar to a restaurant in jacksonville i loved.
Staff is always timely even when they have a full house. I'll return friends next time. Bring your hunger - portions are filling.

Describing this place as elegance would be an understatement.  The atmosphere, the service. The etiquette.  Absolutely phenomenal.  Frank was our waiter and he clearly has been educated on the art of etiquette.  Serving the head of table first.  Food speaks for itself. All i’m going to say is that the chef literally has his personal information on thr menu.  I cannot wait to come back. I’m spreading the word for sure.

Absolutely Amazing! A lovely ambiance with phenomenal food, service and attention to detail in quality. Beautiful wine selection too.  Extremely affordable for outstanding authentic French fare. I kind of want to keep it a secret for myself but everyone should come here and support this gem of a restaurant.

Went to brunch here this afternoon. The seating was very spacious and they did a great job following social sustaining guidelines. It was a really nice experience. The food was delicious. I recommend their peach brioche French toast and avocado toast. Both amazing. Their drinks are also tasty.  Juan, our waiter, was EXCELLENT. He provided great recommendations, demonstrating that he really knew the menu well, and was very accommodating and kind. He checked on us often. We will definitely be coming back to see Juan!

Great French styled brunch spot! A little pricier then what I normally prefer for brunch, but hey, it’s downtown Chicago,  and the excellent service & food made it worth it. The all-you-can-drink mimosas are a great deal, although dangerous!  Our server did not skimp on the pour! My wild mushroom omelette and potatoes were delicious. Big portions.

Wow! What a meal! Authentic French food in downtown Chicago. I got the prixe fixe menu with the gnocchi appetizer which I ate too fast to take a picture! Wonderful staff and service. There was live music for Bastille Day and the chef walked the tables asking how we were enjoying everything. Truly enjoyable evening.

Absolutely amazing dinner😍😍everything we ordered was delicious and beyond expectation. I’m only giving them 4 stars because it took forever for the food to arrive. Reservation was 7:15; seated at around 7:30, and waited for about 20 minutes for someone to take our order. Entree arrived around 8:30 and dessert arrived at 9:15. I’m giving them the benefit of the doubt because of COVID, will return after the virus is gone to see if that’s the norm.
Friendly staff, accessible and affordable french cuisine. Their sauces are top knotch, try their handmade sweet potato gnocchi for your main.

This was a wonderful dinner in every possible way! The staff were friendly and extremely attentive and it was clear to us how much they appreciated our being there. The atmosphere was relaxed and romantic, and most importantly, the food was SPECTACULAR! I can't believe I hadn't eaten there before, but I will absolutely go again!

You will not be disappointed. Between the friendly yet accessible staff, the ambiance, and the thoughtfully prepared delicious meals this is a place to go when you're looking for a very nice night out. This is only the 2nd place I've been to since this phase of re-opening. Our party of 5 was seated on their patio well more than 6 feet away from other diners, and when it started to rain they seamlessly moved us to a sheltered place still a safe distance from others. Staff wore masks and gloves and beared the heat and humidity without batting a lash. I am so grateful to finally have had this delicious French meal, coursed out beautifully, perfectly balanced, just the right amount of attention to details, flavor, presentation. We had soups, escargot, scallops, ahi tuna salad, lamb, rib eye, cocktails, wine, we tried 4 different desserts! We have really been missing dining out, so we went all out tonight, and I'm glad we did it here. Thank you to Bistronomic and all their staff, the food and service was exceptional!!
The spot is great and roomy, the menu was delightful and the rates were very fair. quick, efficient service and very affable staff. Highly recommended.
Recommend the duck and the pasta and truffle pomme frites! For dessert the chocolate bars and baked alaska!

I have not had a meal this delicious in a long time. Just wonderful! They offer 3 and 4 course combination meals, as well as their full menu. Enjoyed a watermelon salad appetizer. But my words do not do it justice. It was unique, flavorful and beautiful. Then I had the duck. What can I say. All served by a fantastic waiter named Raul. It was great.

First time trying French food. Very impressed. I went as part of Chicago’s restaurant week and I’m glad we chose this one. Our waiter was super friendly and had great wine recommendations! The food was obviously so delicious and the atmosphere was pleasant. Everyone was very friendly.

We ate here for restaurant week.  The waiter Raul was exceptional!  He made sure we knew the key points of the menu and his recommendations were perfect. The veloute was well flavored and rich. The  steak was extra tender without the usual tenderizer flavor other restaurants rely on.  The duck with date couscous just hits the palate in all the good ways.  The bread pudding was a deliciously unique preparation that was blended into a cupcake shape and had a French toast flair to it which perfectly complimented the cherries. If you are feeling seafood, the lobster pasta was well flavored and left a pleasant aftertaste.
Great food and phenomenal service from Raoul.  Made my wife’s birthday a very special time with our family.
Excellent and flavorful food, I liked the vibes this spot has, and the cashiers were helpful. Will definitely visit here next time.

Excellent. Great food and service. Space is a little cramped but it’s in the middle of the city so forgivable. Overall a great experience.
Really great take on classic French cuisine, and also a few standards for more conservative diners.

This place was phenomenal. The entire dinner experience was beautiful from the second we walked in the door. Staff was friendly and knowledgeable, and super helpful when we had questions about the menu. I ordered the scallops, which melted in my mouth, so good. We shared the tartare, which was also unbelievably tasty. It is a little pricey for me personally, but definitely worth the cost for a special evening out.
Authentic French restaurant with excellent food and a great ambiance.

I've been a Native Chicagoan most of my life and I've passed by this french bistro numerous times without knowing what I was missing until last Monday evening.  Well now I know what I missed and I'm definitely going to visit again this month!  I arrived at 7pm by myself and I chose a booth table and was seated with fresh baked bread and a menu to peruse.  I looked over everything briefly and decided on the special prix fixe dinner with a choice of appetizers, main course and dessert.  I decided upon the tuna tartare which came in a cute glass jar accompanied by crispy toast points.  It had just the right taste, texture and more than enough toast points so I didn't need to ask for extra. My main course was the seafood linguine which was buttery and rich tasting.  There were peas, salmon and steamed mussels in the shell all with a decadent herb butter taste. The noodles tasted homemade rather than store made so if you love good pasta you won't be disappointed.  After dinner came dessert and so I selected Baked Alaska which was a combination of homemade vanilla ice cream, butterscotch syrup and meringue . This was my first time ever trying a baked Alaska and I'm certain this might be the specialty dessert they cook extremely well and so I truly recommend everyone try it. My waiter was extremely attentive and the service was excellent because everyone here works as a team and once I finished one course the next delicious delicacy came to me within 6 minutes.  It's cozy here and unpretentious so I'm looking forward to future visits.
Very good meal and great service.
I had a fantastic special seafood pasta with mussels and salmon! Extremely recommended 😋
This is a great French bistro. Martial is great

By far the best filet mignon I have ever had. The waiter was attentive and the Chef came out to greet us as well.

First time dining here and we will definitely go back.  We arrived right when they opened at 5:00PM on Sunday and were seated at a very comfortable booth.  French music playing at a pleasant level in the background so everyone at the table could enjoy the lively art of conversation with our visitors from out of town.  Everyone enjoyed their dinners of either scallops or steak and of course dessert with great lattes.  Very pleasant dining experience!
It took around 30 minutes server to come to take our orders. He never brought the latte cafe that we ordered. One of the glasses smelled very bad. Food was ok, but it wasn’t justified for the price.
Phenomenal French food... absolutely divine! For more pictures of food adventures follow me on Instagram @wdouglaskhin

Legitimate French food like I remember from being in France - perhaps with somewhat larger American portions, but is that really a problem? Service is attentive without being overbearing, and you will not be rushed in the least. The prix fixe menu is a great deal and the wine list is solid with a good variety. Nice decor as well - this is the full package.

Bistronomic was outstanding, and the mimosas were flowing. We had the most excellent server Isidro, that truly treated us to a perfect start to our Saturday. We came to Bistronomic on a short notice. The lovely hostess Hilary and Lulu were just the sweetest most accommodating women. They made my friends and I feel at home. Our server Ilir was very attentive and took care of us. Highly recommend the mimosas here. Thank you for a great experience. We will surely be coming back.
Good service really makes a good meal great. Thank you for a very nice evening.

Very customer service-oriented, but wanted to like the food more than we did. Credit for trying to make the effort to deliver high-end plates, but seemed to miss the mark on seasoning most of the dishes we ordered based on our experience that night (went with 2 other friends).

I ate here two years ago for brunch. It is so delicious,  I still remember my experience like it was yesterday. It came up on my timeline along with the photos of my food. My friends were in Chicago visiting me while I was there for work. I wanted to do a boozy brunch and this was one of the few restaurants at the time that had what I was looking for. They offered an entree and a bottomless  mimosas for a price that I don't remember. My drink was never empty. The service was amazing and the burger...... omg like legit best burger of my life. To this day I still remember that burger. I asked for it rare and they cooked it just the way I like it. The fries were perfection and the creme brulee was on point. My friends and I were in food heaven. If im ever in the city again I will definitely come back.

One way to consider how much you enjoy a place is the quality of food and service during a holiday. I've been coming here for a few years, mostly for brunch. One Thanksgiving, a group of friends and I had plans for the holiday weekend, but not on the actual holiday. We got reservations due to a cancellation. Unlike many places, we weren't confined to scheduled seating times, nor a small menu. They offered specials for the holiday, but also their normal dinner menu. Service was spot-on as it usually is. All of our meals were lovely and delicious.  In general, this is not a "bistro" as Americans usually expect. If you're after the typical bistro fare, like onion soup gratín and steak with pommes frites, they offer them, but it's not their strong suit. The less typical dishes are what really shine here. Meats and fish are prepared perfectly, perhaps "delicately" compared to some heavier French dishes. Flavors are subtle, but defined. Vegetables are fresh and used to beautifully emphasize the dishes they're served with. Daytime there is more casual, and for brunch they've got a great waffle served with eggs and bacon. Service has always been great and they've always been accommodating in every way.

I had been searching for a go-to French restaurant in Chicago for a while—after dining here for lunch during Restaurant Week, I concluded that I found that restaurant. For our starter, we had the celeriac soup, which was a delicious, rich soup made with celery root. I had the duck for my main, and the profiteroles for my dessert. What I liked about Bistronomic was that their dishes were French dishes served with a modern twist. Service was good (slightly slow near the end when we were waiting for our dessert), and the waiter was cute with his French accent. Slightly annoyed that the final charge applied to my credit card was off by a few dollars, but I’m going to give the waiter the benefit of the doubt  that it was an honest mistake (only because he was cute).

Bottomless mimosa brunch... Yes, I'm a fan! Made a reservation on Saturday morning at 10:30am but probably didn't need it. Also, warning, the patio is small, probably seats 6 on one end, 6 on the other, and maybe 8 on high boys.  However, the staff is VERY accommodating and figured out a way to get a large party out there without disrupting the foot traffic.  One thing that really impressed me here is the service.  Everyone was coming by to refill water and mimosas and clear plates and were genuinely very nice.  We were also on the struggle bus, so our waiter was so patient with us!  Food wise, this is brunch fare kicked up a notch.  I had the club which was great, with super yummy bacon, and their fries are to die for.
